1
00:00:41,792 --> 00:00:45,963
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:49,591 --> 00:00:53,428
<i>Have you heard of the ill-omened star?</i>

3
00:00:53,512 --> 00:00:55,681
<i>I'm sure you all remember</i>
<i>the recent cosmic show</i>

4
00:00:55,764 --> 00:00:58,517
<i>where a total solar eclipse</i>
<i>and a comet appeared together.</i>

5
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:02,646
<i>Well, that comet is</i>
<i>still in the sky today.</i>

6
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:04,856
That's really amazing.

7
00:01:04,940 --> 00:01:06,191
<i>Three hundred years ago,</i>

8
00:01:06,275 --> 00:01:09,027
<i>when our ancestors noticed a comet</i>
<i>lingering for two months,</i>

9
00:01:09,111 --> 00:01:12,155
<i>they called it the ill-omened star.</i>

10
00:01:12,864 --> 00:01:16,660
<i>The herald of a villainess</i>
<i>who brings disaster.</i>

11
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:18,579
You pity me?

12
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:45,105
I guess he just can't ignore that woman.

13
00:01:45,606 --> 00:01:46,898
THE WOMAN POSSESSED BY KIM DU-HAN

14
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,110
Unit 203?

15
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:51,194
What the…

16
00:01:53,322 --> 00:01:54,990
She's resorted to throwing punches now.

17
00:01:55,073 --> 00:01:58,452
<i>So, take a good look around you.</i>

18
00:01:58,535 --> 00:01:59,703
<i>You never know.</i>

19
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:02,998
<i>You might discover there's</i>
<i>a wicked woman living right next door.</i>

20
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,542
I have to keep my distance from her.

21
00:02:05,626 --> 00:02:07,628
That woman just creeps me out.

22
00:02:07,711 --> 00:02:10,631
He’s going to get
seriously tangled up with her.

23
00:02:11,423 --> 00:02:13,383
Why do our paths keep crossing?

24
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:15,135
I'm about to lose it.

25
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:19,097
EPISODE 5
FORBIDDEN FRUIT

26
00:02:19,181 --> 00:02:20,307
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

27
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:27,272
She acts like she's so smart.

28
00:02:27,898 --> 00:02:30,317
Did she just get scammed
by her realtor or what?

29
00:02:32,235 --> 00:02:34,488
There's not even an elevator here.

30
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:40,035
And the lights don't even work.

31
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:12,401
Are you crying?

32
00:03:20,117 --> 00:03:22,911
Are you really crying,
hunched over like that?

33
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:33,547
What?

34
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:36,007
Why are you back to pick another fight?

35
00:03:36,091 --> 00:03:38,760
That's more like the Shin Seo-ri I know.

36
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:44,891
So she's just some random model,
nothing more?

37
00:03:44,975 --> 00:03:45,851
Yes, sir.

38
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:48,520
He was initially opposed to it,

39
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:51,064
but Director Jang
strongly recommended her.

40
00:03:51,148 --> 00:03:52,023
Really?

41
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:55,986
I should've known better.

42
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:59,406
What was he thinking,
linking my Se-gye with that woman?

43
00:04:11,543 --> 00:04:14,004
Are you still checking if you're unfazed?

44
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:16,089
I think this is more than enough.

45
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:19,843
No, I finished a while ago,

46
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:21,136
but you were staying so still.

47
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:23,180
I just thought you were still checking.

48
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:26,224
I finished a while ago too.

49
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,061
Yeah?

50
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:35,233
So what's the conclusion?

51
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:39,571
Must you press me like a debt collector?

52
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:42,199
I already told you.

53
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:45,410
I see in black or white.
You're either an ally or an enemy.

54
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:47,454
I hate it when men and women

55
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:49,915
end up in that "just friends" gray area.

56
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:51,458
So give it to me straight.

57
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:55,545
Why should I go first? You answer first.

58
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:56,755
Well…

59
00:04:58,632 --> 00:04:59,716
All right.

60
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:04,513
It’s cowardly for a man
to expect a woman to make the first move.

61
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:06,556
I hate it when things get predictable.

62
00:05:11,102 --> 00:05:12,229
All right.

63
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,732
I decided it's a green light

64
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:16,858
for me.

65
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:22,489
You turned on a lantern?

66
00:05:22,572 --> 00:05:24,533
I've decided to pursue you.

67
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:27,452
Jeez.

68
00:05:30,956 --> 00:05:31,998
How do you feel?

69
00:05:32,624 --> 00:05:33,583
Honored, right?

70
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:35,085
Heir to the Chail Group

71
00:05:35,168 --> 00:05:36,795
and the finest face
in the corporate world.

72
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:39,297
I've had plenty of people declare
their love for me,

73
00:05:39,381 --> 00:05:41,716
but I've never gone
on the offensive like this.

74
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:48,557
It seems you're so touched,
you can't even find the words.

75
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:51,852
Well, I understand.
Your heart must've skipped a beat,

76
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:54,771
and your nerve endings
must be tingling like crazy, right?

77
00:05:54,855 --> 00:05:55,856
Relish it.

78
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:56,857
Because this is

79
00:05:56,940 --> 00:06:00,652
a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity
for a woman like you.

80
00:06:03,405 --> 00:06:05,365
I did not feel any tingling.

81
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:11,663
It probably hasn't sunk in yet.
You're still reeling from the shock.

82
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:13,123
Give it five minutes.

83
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:14,624
Even your fingertips will tingle.

84
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:16,793
Shin Seo-ri, you won't sleep tonight.

85
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:18,670
I feel absolutely nothing.

86
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:21,423
Even when we embraced, I felt nothing.

87
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:23,758
That's impossible.

88
00:06:23,842 --> 00:06:27,262
You were just in the arms of a guy
like me, dripping with pheromones.

89
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:35,478
Don't lie, Shin Seo-ri.

90
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:38,064
Don't put up a front now
and regret it later.

91
00:06:38,148 --> 00:06:40,191
This is no front.
I was just born strong-willed.

92
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:41,776
Also,

93
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:44,321
I do not go around telling needless lies.

94
00:06:45,989 --> 00:06:47,949
Wait, are you serious?

95
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:52,996
You really feel nothing?

96
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,539
- Even after <i>I</i> hugged you?
- Nothing.

97
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:01,713
That can't be right.

98
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:05,967
You definitely should've felt what I felt.

99
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:16,436
I wasn't going to ask you this,

100
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:19,481
but have you been perpetually single
your whole life?

101
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:22,233
"Perpetually single"?

102
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:24,694
Have you never dated a man before?

103
00:07:26,237 --> 00:07:27,113
As if.

104
00:07:27,197 --> 00:07:28,615
At this age? With this beauty?

105
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,116
Like men would have left me alone.

106
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,160
- Ridiculous.
- Right?

107
00:07:32,744 --> 00:07:33,745
Yeah.

108
00:07:34,955 --> 00:07:36,915
Then why didn't you feel anything with me?

109
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:38,708
Does asking repeatedly change anything?

110
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:41,294
I do not see you as a man.

111
00:07:41,378 --> 00:07:42,712
That must be what it means.

112
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,596
Wait, what?

113
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:54,015
It is raining! Oh my.

114
00:08:18,123 --> 00:08:20,250
<i>Keep a close eye on him.</i>

115
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:24,337
Mun-do wouldn't mention baseless rumors.

116
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:27,007
That woman he saw at the TV station.

117
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:29,300
Find out who she is.

118
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:34,639
At the station? Then it can only be her.

119
00:08:37,809 --> 00:08:39,227
True to your name, Degenerate.

120
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:40,687
Even if it is raining,

121
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:43,440
you cannot just walk into the home
of a single woman who lives alone.

122
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,567
- You really felt nothing?
- Are you still on that?

123
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:47,777
That is right. I felt nothing.

124
00:08:47,861 --> 00:08:49,904
It was less thrilling
than hugging a stray mutt.

125
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:51,239
"A mutt"?

126
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:52,741
So stop moping around

127
00:08:52,824 --> 00:08:54,534
and go home!

128
00:08:57,245 --> 00:08:59,706
Maybe you felt nothing
because it was too quick.

129
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:02,500
You've been single for too long.

130
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:05,795
Your romantic instincts are dead.
It sounds like you need a warm-up.

131
00:09:05,879 --> 00:09:07,505
Let's try again. Then I'm sure you'll--

132
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:10,008
This is getting pitiful.
Just stop, Cha Se-gye.

133
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:11,718
"Pitiful"?

134
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:13,970
Me?

135
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:17,807
They say never chase a maiden
who has walked away.

136
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,059
This is my home,

137
00:09:19,142 --> 00:09:21,269
so just let it go gracefully.

138
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,731
After not dating for so long,
you must've become

139
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:26,149
romantically impotent.

140
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:29,277
You must know an opportunity like this
is rarer than winning the lottery.

141
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,488
Even with three generations of good karma,

142
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,782
the chances of such a jackpot are slim.

143
00:09:33,865 --> 00:09:35,492
For one, I am not impotent.

144
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,660
And affection, love,
and marriage in this lifetime?

145
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,287
I want no part of any of that.

146
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:42,123
I never want to get involved
with a man again.

147
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:45,168
So stop being so pathetically clingy.

148
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:46,377
Jeez.

149
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:49,172
"Pathetically"?

150
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:51,508
Damn,

151
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,843
you must think you have
the upper hand now or something.

152
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:57,263
Shin Seo-ri, that's one hell
of a shift in attitude.

153
00:09:57,347 --> 00:09:58,932
What you just said.

154
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:02,102
I've permanently etched it
into my frontal lobe.

155
00:10:03,186 --> 00:10:04,687
You can't ever take it back.

156
00:10:05,355 --> 00:10:06,731
Do not worry about that.

157
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:08,900
Even in a game of <i>janggi,</i>

158
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:11,903
I have never once asked
to take back a move.

159
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:18,701
You're so damn immersed
in this Joseon woman roleplay

160
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:20,537
that you must've lost touch with reality.

161
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,914
I will make sure…

162
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:27,502
you regret this moment
for the rest of your life.

163
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,087
I will.

164
00:10:34,134 --> 00:10:35,135
Damn it.

165
00:10:52,277 --> 00:10:54,821
My heart was about
to jump out of my chest.

166
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:57,323
Why the hell
would he just embrace me like that?

167
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,743
Don't you have an umbrella?

168
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:01,786
No, I do not!

169
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,997
What <i>does</i> this dump even have?

170
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:08,626
What is wrong with my home?

171
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:10,879
It even has a clear view of Namsan Tower!

172
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:28,897
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

173
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:37,197
Who the hell did this?!

174
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:50,668
That's a nasty scratch.

175
00:11:51,294 --> 00:11:53,671
The repair cost will be insane.
You checked the dashcam, right?

176
00:11:53,755 --> 00:11:55,131
Just take it in for repairs later.

177
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:57,467
Even a chaebol shouldn't let
something like this slide.

178
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:59,761
Just forget it.
That dashcam might as well be a tin can.

179
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:01,137
You didn't turn it on?

180
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:04,265
How does someone as thorough
as you forget something like this?

181
00:12:04,349 --> 00:12:06,392
Do you really think I just forgot?

182
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:09,270
I turned it off on purpose.
I mean, why would I leave evidence

183
00:12:09,354 --> 00:12:10,688
they could use against me?

184
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:19,322
It's the dashcam footage nailing people
in these power-trip scandals.

185
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:21,991
Straight to the prosecutors
with nowhere to run.

186
00:12:22,617 --> 00:12:25,745
You should never leave a trail
to begin with.

187
00:12:27,956 --> 00:12:29,582
You're way too paranoid.

188
00:12:32,126 --> 00:12:33,002
BUILT-IN CAM

189
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:34,587
NO MEMORY CARD

190
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:37,966
Sir, don't tell me
you don't trust me either.

191
00:12:38,049 --> 00:12:40,677
In today's world, isn't this level
of distrust the default?

192
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,971
I don't trust anyone in this world.
You are not exempt.

193
00:12:43,054 --> 00:12:44,931
I only trust myself, no one else.

194
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:48,142
You'll have a lonely life
if you keep living that way.

195
00:12:48,226 --> 00:12:52,105
I've had everything I could ever want.
What do I have to be lonely about?

196
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:53,815
You don't have a woman.

197
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:56,025
Destined to die alone.

198
00:13:00,363 --> 00:13:01,739
- Mr. Son.
- Yes, sir.

199
00:13:01,823 --> 00:13:04,033
It seems like I've let you
get too comfortable lately.

200
00:13:05,076 --> 00:13:08,538
We seem to have lost
all sense of hierarchy.

201
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:11,582
- Watch yourself.
- I will watch myself.

202
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:14,460
- Keep your eyes on the road.
- Keeping my eyes on the road.

203
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:16,754
- Seer.
- Yes?

204
00:13:16,838 --> 00:13:19,257
I assume you prepared what I asked for?

205
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:22,093
Of course.

206
00:13:32,895 --> 00:13:34,105
There we go.

207
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:41,863
Hold the elevator.

208
00:13:41,946 --> 00:13:44,991
Oh my. Good morning, Mr. Cha.

209
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:49,954
Ms. Kim, you seem
awfully happy with life these days.

210
00:13:51,039 --> 00:13:53,291
"I don't smile because I'm happy.
I smile to be happy."

211
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:54,584
That is my motto.

212
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:59,255
You have time to gleefully find happiness
and energy to spare, I see.

213
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:02,633
Then we can just cancel
your PTO this month, right?

214
00:14:02,717 --> 00:14:04,135
My PTO…

215
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:10,975
I already booked a trip to Saipan
for my father-in-law's 70th.

216
00:14:11,059 --> 00:14:13,770
You have to go to that.
Pass him my congratulations.

217
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:17,982
They will appreciate a cozy getaway
without their daughter-in-law.

218
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:22,195
Graciously sending them off on their own.
Isn't that true filial piety?

219
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:38,836
Mr. Son, there's something
I don't understand.

220
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:42,048
Why do we need snacks
and coffee in the break room?

221
00:14:42,131 --> 00:14:45,176
It's for staff welfare purposes.

222
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:47,929
That's what salaries are for, isn't it?

223
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:49,806
Should we be dedicating
such prime real estate

224
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:53,101
to a snack corner just so employees
can munch away on company time?

225
00:14:53,184 --> 00:14:54,852
Close the break room immediately.

226
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,156
Why is he in rabid dog mode again?

227
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,242
Just when things were looking up.

228
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,035
Be careful at times like this.

229
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:13,955
He's the type to let things build up
and explode all at once.

230
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,333
- Mr. Son.
- Sir.

231
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,627
I like those quick reflexes, Mr. Son.

232
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:21,045
Stay on full standby.

233
00:15:25,091 --> 00:15:26,551
He's sick in the head.

234
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:33,891
Is your cheek okay?

235
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:37,019
I gave that punk Se-gye a real scolding.

236
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:38,896
Swinging at people like some common thug…

237
00:15:38,980 --> 00:15:40,231
I'm fine, Uncle.

238
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:43,860
Mun-do, I must ask you to be
the bigger person.

239
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:46,654
Don't worry. I understand.

240
00:15:48,114 --> 00:15:51,617
More importantly, the press release
for the Songjin Resort groundbreaking

241
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:52,869
was received well.

242
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,705
It's all thanks to your foresight.

243
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:58,958
How many struggling subsidiaries
have you resurrected already?

244
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:03,045
With you providing such solid support,

245
00:16:03,129 --> 00:16:04,797
I think it's about time

246
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:07,300
we start looking

247
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:09,635
into the group succession issue.

248
00:16:09,719 --> 00:16:13,014
Just wrap up the resort deal well.

249
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:14,932
Yes, sir.

250
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,977
Chairman, Attorney Choi is here.

251
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,020
Okay.

252
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:21,397
- You can go now.
- Yes, Uncle.

253
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:03,189
They're notarized documents.

254
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:05,608
They outline the full transfer
of Chairman Cha's shareholding

255
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:06,901
across all subsidiaries,

256
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:09,654
holding company included,
to Mr. Cha Se-gye.

257
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:10,613
Does Se-gye know?

258
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,448
Inheritance notarization can be processed

259
00:17:12,532 --> 00:17:14,867
with just a resident ID number.
No consent required.

260
00:17:14,951 --> 00:17:17,119
Chairman Cha didn't want
Mr. Cha to know about it.

261
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:23,251
Our Chairman…

262
00:17:24,794 --> 00:17:26,879
sure loves his grandson fiercely.

263
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:37,640
Will using coagulated ox blood like this
really ward off bad luck?

264
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,308
We must work with what we have got.

265
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:42,478
You know, after 20 years as a seer,

266
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:44,272
there's one thing I've learned.

267
00:17:44,355 --> 00:17:47,024
The cumulative law of suffering
does indeed exist.

268
00:17:47,108 --> 00:17:48,901
You found a job

269
00:17:48,985 --> 00:17:50,361
and even found yourself a home.

270
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:52,154
I mean, just look at you.

271
00:17:52,238 --> 00:17:54,407
Seems like your days of hardship
are nearly done.

272
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,492
Good luck invites bad. Such is life.

273
00:17:56,576 --> 00:17:57,952
Yes, of course.

274
00:17:58,035 --> 00:18:01,622
People will always find a way to stab you
in the back when you let your guard down.

275
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:05,251
I am doing this warding ritual
so I can at least have some peace of mind.

276
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:08,963
What warding ritual?

277
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:16,178
<i>At age 12, the day I was sold off</i>
<i>for my father's gambling debt,</i>

278
00:18:16,721 --> 00:18:18,723
<i>I learned my first life lesson.</i>

279
00:18:19,682 --> 00:18:22,893
What a gloomy face on this girl.
Bad luck written all over it.

280
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:25,229
Keep acting this way,

281
00:18:25,313 --> 00:18:28,024
and there will be
nothing left of you to find.

282
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:29,317
Jeez.

283
00:18:31,402 --> 00:18:32,820
Do not worry.

284
00:18:32,903 --> 00:18:36,115
Being a slave to a noble family
that keeps you fed

285
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:38,367
beats starving at home
a hundred times over.

286
00:18:39,827 --> 00:18:41,078
Here.

287
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:43,247
Go on. Have some.

288
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,124
Just try it.

289
00:18:47,585 --> 00:18:50,004
Crying on an empty stomach
will only exhaust you.

290
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,132
My goodness.

291
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:58,888
<i>Free kindness always comes with a price.</i>

292
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,765
Here. That is plenty.

293
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:04,018
Come on, I deserve
five more <i>nyang</i> for her.

294
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:05,978
Look at that pretty face.

295
00:19:06,062 --> 00:19:08,481
She will seduce plenty of men
when she grows up.

296
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,441
If you sell her
to a courtesan house later,

297
00:19:10,524 --> 00:19:12,568
she will fetch you enough
to buy a house in Bukchon.

298
00:19:12,652 --> 00:19:14,403
- Trust me on this.
- Really? A house?

299
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:18,199
<i>Never trust a hand</i>
<i>reached out with a smile.</i>

300
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:20,534
- What?
- Hey!

301
00:19:20,618 --> 00:19:22,578
- Hey!
- Where are you going?

302
00:19:22,662 --> 00:19:23,704
You brat!

303
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:26,707
Damn it.

304
00:19:26,791 --> 00:19:27,708
Unbelievable.

305
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:30,628
Goodness.

306
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:33,839
<i>Lock her in the shed.</i>
<i>Do not give her a drop of water.</i>

307
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:45,059
<i>I swore to myself back then</i>

308
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:49,772
<i>that I would never trust</i>
<i>anyone but myself.</i>

309
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:52,942
<i>That I would never be sold off</i>
<i>like livestock again.</i>

310
00:20:01,659 --> 00:20:04,328
<i>I'm rooting for you two.</i>

311
00:20:04,412 --> 00:20:06,080
<i>I can promise you a real future.</i>

312
00:20:06,831 --> 00:20:08,457
A life of comfort.

313
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:17,007
Wait, is someone trying
to sell you off here too?

314
00:20:17,091 --> 00:20:20,177
He promised a hefty reward
if I agreed to be sold.

315
00:20:21,679 --> 00:20:24,724
I will not make the mistake of falling

316
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:27,184
for such sweet talk ever again.

317
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,773
But don't you think
you'll get a little lonely

318
00:20:32,857 --> 00:20:34,400
if you live your life like that?

319
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:36,819
Not all of them will turn out

320
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:38,612
to be scammers.

321
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:41,365
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

322
00:20:44,452 --> 00:20:46,787
The world may be a harsh place,

323
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:50,207
but not everyone in it means you harm.

324
00:20:53,586 --> 00:20:55,629
That is why I must steel my resolve.

325
00:20:56,547 --> 00:20:58,007
Scammer or not,

326
00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:00,176
once your heart wavers, you become weak.

327
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:02,845
In my current situation,
weakness means the end.

328
00:21:03,554 --> 00:21:05,598
Thus, I have decided.

329
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:07,850
In this life, I will not trust anyone.

330
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:09,018
Instead, I shall become

331
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:11,604
a wealthy Buddhist nun
on a path to enlightenment.

332
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:15,816
A wealthy… Buddhist nun, you say?

333
00:21:17,026 --> 00:21:19,236
The only constant in this world is money.

334
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,863
Ought we not serve it?

335
00:21:21,697 --> 00:21:24,950
When I open my window,
I can already see Namsan Tower.

336
00:21:25,785 --> 00:21:27,953
I escaped that dump
in the blink of an eye,

337
00:21:28,037 --> 00:21:31,165
so I shall use this momentum to soar high.

338
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:42,218
Sounds good!

339
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:50,726
She feels nothing for me?

340
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:53,145
Acting tough is only cute up to a point.

341
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:58,859
She's the one who messed with my head
with that letter and everything.

342
00:22:00,236 --> 00:22:02,571
I've never been so humiliated in my life.

343
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:05,866
<i>Known as the heir to one of the top 30…</i>

344
00:22:05,950 --> 00:22:07,034
What now?

345
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:08,536
<i>Controversy is brewing</i>

346
00:22:08,619 --> 00:22:10,955
<i>after it was revealed</i>
<i>that Mr. Cha repeatedly used</i>

347
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:14,083
<i>intimidation tactics</i>
<i>while acquiring a small business</i>

348
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:16,001
<i>for his startup brand launch.</i>

349
00:22:17,044 --> 00:22:18,087
<i>You're going to have to.</i>

350
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:20,005
<i>This is your first and last chance</i>

351
00:22:20,089 --> 00:22:22,591
<i>to get even a pittance</i>
<i>for that measly company of yours.</i>

352
00:22:22,675 --> 00:22:24,718
<i>The price drops by a billion won</i>
<i>every ten seconds.</i>

353
00:22:24,802 --> 00:22:27,221
<i>Even now, thinking about being</i>
<i>extorted and bled dry</i>

354
00:22:27,304 --> 00:22:28,889
<i>by someone young enough to be my son</i>

355
00:22:28,973 --> 00:22:30,558
<i>cuts me to the core.</i>

356
00:22:30,641 --> 00:22:33,352
<i>The spokesperson stressed it is time</i>
<i>for the Fair Trade Commission</i>

357
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:35,521
<i>to crack down and put an end</i>

358
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:38,649
<i>to these diabolical acts of preying</i>
<i>on the small businesses</i>

359
00:22:38,732 --> 00:22:41,777
<i>that keep Korea's economy running.</i>

360
00:22:41,861 --> 00:22:45,656
I let you off with money instead
of handcuffs, and this is what I get?

361
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:47,074
I stole your livelihood?

362
00:22:47,157 --> 00:22:50,369
He must've found out the raw materials
got FDA approval right after the sale,

363
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:52,246
leaving him feeling bitter.

364
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:54,415
I'm in the headlines a lot lately.

365
00:22:54,498 --> 00:22:55,499
Any stock impact?

366
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:57,751
It's plateauing around 87,000 won,

367
00:22:57,835 --> 00:22:59,879
but they haven't
publicly identified you yet.

368
00:22:59,962 --> 00:23:02,715
I'll have the legal team handle it
before it becomes a risk factor.

369
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:03,716
<i>Don't worry.</i>

370
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,009
No, I should worry.

371
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:07,094
Without any upward catalysts
before the launch,

372
00:23:07,177 --> 00:23:08,762
even 80,000 won is precarious.

373
00:23:08,846 --> 00:23:11,223
Leave the legal team out of it.
We'll tackle this head-on.

374
00:23:11,307 --> 00:23:13,559
- "Head-on"?
- He's not relying on legalities right now.

375
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:15,352
He's looking to whip up public sentiment.

376
00:23:15,436 --> 00:23:16,812
Then we go eye for an eye.

377
00:23:16,896 --> 00:23:19,440
Forget the law.
We need to rattle his nerves.

378
00:23:19,523 --> 00:23:20,983
<i>Leak it all to the tabloids.</i>

379
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:23,110
The photos of him gallivanting
around Kangwon Land Casino

380
00:23:23,193 --> 00:23:24,361
after pocketing employee bonuses

381
00:23:24,445 --> 00:23:27,239
and every last piece of evidence
of the cheap raw material swap.

382
00:23:27,323 --> 00:23:30,534
Expose that fake saint
for the fraud he is.

383
00:23:30,618 --> 00:23:31,911
Yes, sir.

384
00:23:31,994 --> 00:23:34,121
RUTHLESS CHAEBOL STEALS
LIVELIHOOD OF SMALL BUSINESSES

385
00:23:35,497 --> 00:23:38,167
I keep them out of prison,
and they stab me in the back.

386
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:40,961
Nobody knows how to be grateful anymore.

387
00:23:41,587 --> 00:23:42,880
<i>Thank you.</i>

388
00:23:42,963 --> 00:23:45,424
I have met many people here,

389
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:48,052
but you have been the kindest to me,
and I am most thankful.

390
00:23:48,135 --> 00:23:50,262
That is right. I felt nothing.

391
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:53,432
It was less thrilling
than hugging a stray mutt.

392
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:55,726
Does she suffer
from multiple personalities?

393
00:23:56,894 --> 00:24:00,439
Hot one minute, cold the next.
Is she playing hard to get or something?

394
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:07,863
She's actually playing hard to get.

395
00:24:13,369 --> 00:24:15,871
- Manager Gu.
- She took it too far.

396
00:24:15,955 --> 00:24:17,039
- Uncle!
- Manager Gu.

397
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:18,123
- Uncle.
- Uncle!

398
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:19,458
- Wake up, Uncle.
- What?

399
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:21,627
- Uncle, wake up.
- What's up?

400
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:23,796
You need to deal
with that mess on the roof!

401
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:28,550
I've told her so many times
to watch the noise!

402
00:24:28,634 --> 00:24:31,095
What the… What is all this?

403
00:24:32,972 --> 00:24:35,099
Rooftop, what in the world is going on…

404
00:24:42,481 --> 00:24:45,734
<i>Hail, boundless life!</i>

405
00:24:47,111 --> 00:24:51,448
<i>Hail, the Great Spirit!</i>

406
00:24:52,074 --> 00:24:53,200
Manager Gu.

407
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:55,077
Oh my God!

408
00:24:56,161 --> 00:24:57,538
Manager Gu, are you here

409
00:24:57,621 --> 00:24:59,540
to watch the ritual
and grab some free rice cakes?

410
00:24:59,623 --> 00:25:01,875
B-Bloo… B-Blood…

411
00:25:01,959 --> 00:25:04,795
Right. This is not human blood.
It is coagulated ox blood.

412
00:25:04,878 --> 00:25:06,839
Why would you put on
such a terrifying getup?

413
00:25:06,922 --> 00:25:09,008
I'm about to enter the battlefield,

414
00:25:09,091 --> 00:25:12,177
so I thought I would put some on
to ward off evil.

415
00:25:12,261 --> 00:25:14,138
Want some, Manager Gu?

416
00:25:19,727 --> 00:25:20,978
What was today's closing price?

417
00:25:21,061 --> 00:25:22,563
It closed at 82,000 won.

418
00:25:22,646 --> 00:25:24,440
With today's leak making the rounds,

419
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:27,604
numbers are down slightly
after the deepfake scandal.

420
00:25:27,693 --> 00:25:29,903
Meaning we can't afford any more bad news.

421
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:31,989
For now, send this out with the photos.

422
00:25:32,072 --> 00:25:34,199
Just to the tabloids,
including financial gossip rags.

423
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:35,367
Skip mainstream outlets.

424
00:25:35,451 --> 00:25:37,202
Is that necessary when the PR team

425
00:25:37,286 --> 00:25:39,830
already tipped off the deputy managers
about the raw material swap?

426
00:25:39,913 --> 00:25:42,875
What we need isn't a news story.
We just need a good story.

427
00:25:42,958 --> 00:25:45,044
We're throwing bait
for the public to bite,

428
00:25:45,127 --> 00:25:46,378
so we need to spice it up.

429
00:25:46,462 --> 00:25:48,088
I should've known.

430
00:25:48,172 --> 00:25:50,799
Your disarmingly cunning tactics

431
00:25:50,883 --> 00:25:52,384
are on another level, sir.

432
00:25:52,468 --> 00:25:54,595
- Speaking of which, Mr. Son.
- Yes, sir.

433
00:26:01,935 --> 00:26:03,270
Never mind.

434
00:26:04,688 --> 00:26:05,856
Yes, sir.

435
00:26:08,609 --> 00:26:10,069
Damn it.

436
00:26:20,871 --> 00:26:22,539
Mr. Son, I have a question.

437
00:26:22,623 --> 00:26:24,875
Yes, sir. Go ahead.

438
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:31,423
Well…

439
00:26:32,841 --> 00:26:34,468
- Never mind.
- "Never mind"?

440
00:26:48,565 --> 00:26:49,525
Gosh.

441
00:26:50,317 --> 00:26:52,694
Jeez. What is it? Just tell me.

442
00:26:52,778 --> 00:26:55,072
You've been keeping me
in suspense all day.

443
00:26:55,155 --> 00:26:57,533
Mr. Son, did you just yell at me?

444
00:26:57,616 --> 00:26:59,076
No, of course not.

445
00:26:59,159 --> 00:27:00,494
I wasn't yelling.

446
00:27:00,577 --> 00:27:03,163
I was just urging you to tell me
so you'd be less stressed.

447
00:27:03,247 --> 00:27:05,415
That there is no need for you
to agonize over it.

448
00:27:05,499 --> 00:27:07,918
It was an earnest plea, sir.

449
00:27:09,378 --> 00:27:11,088
Since you're pushing so hard, Mr. Son,

450
00:27:11,171 --> 00:27:13,549
I'll be frank with you.

451
00:27:14,174 --> 00:27:15,634
Between a man and a woman…

452
00:27:16,718 --> 00:27:18,220
when it comes to the push-and-pull,

453
00:27:18,303 --> 00:27:20,514
how do you gain the upper hand?

454
00:27:20,597 --> 00:27:21,807
"The push-and-pull"?

455
00:27:22,850 --> 00:27:25,853
It's the storyline of some drama
I've been watching when I can't sleep.

456
00:27:25,936 --> 00:27:28,105
I just leave it on to fall asleep to.

457
00:27:29,606 --> 00:27:30,774
Well!

458
00:27:30,858 --> 00:27:33,777
The way I see it, timing is everything
when playing hard to get.

459
00:27:33,861 --> 00:27:35,904
The reality is,
you just have to bombard them.

460
00:27:35,988 --> 00:27:37,489
Give them no time to play games.

461
00:27:37,573 --> 00:27:40,409
Because love
is just another form of warfare.

462
00:27:41,118 --> 00:27:42,828
By bombardment, do you mean

463
00:27:42,911 --> 00:27:45,289
just overwhelming them
with a massive offensive?

464
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:47,291
In the war of courtship,
losing is winning.

465
00:27:47,374 --> 00:27:49,668
Just say,
"I surrender! I'll die without you!"

466
00:27:49,751 --> 00:27:51,670
When you throw away all your pride,

467
00:27:51,753 --> 00:27:53,881
that's when you truly gain the upper hand.

468
00:27:54,464 --> 00:27:57,050
So what about you?

469
00:27:57,134 --> 00:27:58,927
Have you won every battle
using that method?

470
00:27:59,011 --> 00:28:00,095
I've lost every battle.

471
00:28:00,179 --> 00:28:02,181
Theory is just theory, after all.

472
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:09,021
- Let's go.
- Right away, sir.

473
00:28:13,275 --> 00:28:15,944
A full-on bombardment
and a massive offensive…

474
00:28:18,906 --> 00:28:22,576
As if you could ever gain the upper hand
with such a cliché strategy.

475
00:28:24,786 --> 00:28:26,455
Isn't there anything else?

476
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:29,666
No. What don't you like about this one?

477
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:31,251
It doesn't fit quite right.

478
00:28:32,961 --> 00:28:34,129
It doesn't look sharp.

479
00:28:34,713 --> 00:28:38,008
It's the exact same cut
as your usual custom jackets.

480
00:28:39,676 --> 00:28:41,303
Is it just me?

481
00:28:41,887 --> 00:28:43,347
It just feels cliché.

482
00:29:00,364 --> 00:29:02,449
I am finally entering the battlefield.

483
00:29:08,497 --> 00:29:09,748
GRANDMA

484
00:29:11,375 --> 00:29:12,251
<i>Who…</i>

485
00:29:12,876 --> 00:29:14,294
are you?

486
00:29:18,507 --> 00:29:19,466
<i>Seo-ri, it's Grandma.</i>

487
00:29:20,133 --> 00:29:22,719
<i>Are you doing okay up there?</i>

488
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:24,513
I am fine.

489
00:29:25,764 --> 00:29:27,099
But is everything okay there?

490
00:29:27,182 --> 00:29:28,725
<i>Is anyone causing trouble again?</i>

491
00:29:28,809 --> 00:29:31,478
No, of course not.
You chased them all away.

492
00:29:31,561 --> 00:29:35,774
But since when were you so agile?

493
00:29:35,857 --> 00:29:37,567
Well, I…

494
00:29:38,151 --> 00:29:40,320
I picked up a few things here and there.

495
00:29:41,363 --> 00:29:44,283
If they swarm in again,
call me right away, okay?

496
00:29:44,366 --> 00:29:45,242
Okay, I will.

497
00:29:45,909 --> 00:29:46,910
Gosh, I have customers.

498
00:29:46,994 --> 00:29:48,453
Don't worry about me, okay?

499
00:29:48,537 --> 00:29:50,455
Make sure you eat well.

500
00:29:50,539 --> 00:29:52,374
<i>Okay, I'm hanging up now.</i>

501
00:29:58,046 --> 00:29:59,673
Seo-ri.

502
00:30:00,299 --> 00:30:02,718
How does it feel to be on set?

503
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,721
It must feel really different,
stepping onto the set this time

504
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:07,556
as Court Lady Kim,

505
00:30:07,639 --> 00:30:09,141
instead of "Palace Attendant 28."

506
00:30:09,224 --> 00:30:12,519
You only scored a role like this
because you have me.

507
00:30:12,602 --> 00:30:15,522
I am not even the Head Court Lady.
Stop making such a fuss.

508
00:30:15,605 --> 00:30:16,690
Not even a single line.

509
00:30:16,773 --> 00:30:18,775
Even without a single line,
you can steal the scene

510
00:30:18,859 --> 00:30:20,861
with just one look, okay?

511
00:30:20,944 --> 00:30:22,321
- Do your best.
- Did you check continuity?

512
00:30:22,404 --> 00:30:24,239
- Yes, confirmed.
- And the CGI?

513
00:30:24,323 --> 00:30:25,824
Gosh. Ms. Hong.

514
00:30:25,907 --> 00:30:29,077
- Director, how have you been?
- You get prettier by the day.

515
00:30:29,161 --> 00:30:31,079
- Who cares about effort?
- You're too sweet.

516
00:30:31,163 --> 00:30:32,539
Results are what matter.

517
00:30:32,622 --> 00:30:33,582
Shin Seo-ri.

518
00:30:35,083 --> 00:30:38,045
You finally got a role, thanks to me.

519
00:30:38,128 --> 00:30:39,504
You should give it your all

520
00:30:39,588 --> 00:30:41,298
and try to hide that you pulled strings.

521
00:30:41,381 --> 00:30:43,133
If you wish for me to do well,

522
00:30:43,216 --> 00:30:45,635
do not hover around me pointlessly.

523
00:30:45,719 --> 00:30:48,889
That face of yours remains
my only irritant in this place.

524
00:30:48,972 --> 00:30:50,724
But remember,
when the cameras are rolling,

525
00:30:50,807 --> 00:30:52,726
I am the Queen,

526
00:30:52,809 --> 00:30:55,896
and <i>you</i> are just a lowly court lady.

527
00:30:55,979 --> 00:30:58,440
Even <i>I</i> can't save you if you can't act.

528
00:30:58,523 --> 00:30:59,733
- Let's go.
- This way.

529
00:31:01,902 --> 00:31:02,986
As if.

530
00:31:03,528 --> 00:31:05,113
Why, that minx…

531
00:31:05,197 --> 00:31:06,907
She is putting on airs

532
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,992
just because she is in the Queen's garb.

533
00:31:09,576 --> 00:31:11,244
What's taking so long?

534
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:15,874
Oh my God!

535
00:31:15,957 --> 00:31:17,751
Gosh. Oh no…

536
00:31:17,834 --> 00:31:18,919
I'm so sorry.

537
00:31:19,002 --> 00:31:20,629
You should watch where you're going.

538
00:31:21,588 --> 00:31:24,758
I'll pay for the dry cleaning.
No, I'll pay for the suit.

539
00:31:24,841 --> 00:31:27,636
You should find out how much it is
before you offer to pay for it.

540
00:31:27,719 --> 00:31:29,638
I'm a regular here too, so I know.

541
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:31,932
It's my fault, so I should compensate you.

542
00:31:32,015 --> 00:31:33,892
I'll pass on that offer.

543
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:37,020
I'm not so poor that I need
to beg for free clothes.

544
00:31:37,104 --> 00:31:38,563
Sir.

545
00:31:40,857 --> 00:31:42,609
- Are you okay?
- Wait, what happened…

546
00:31:42,692 --> 00:31:44,778
Please step this way first.

547
00:31:44,861 --> 00:31:46,696
Just get me a fresh one. Same suit.

548
00:31:46,780 --> 00:31:48,198
And send the rest to my house.

549
00:31:48,281 --> 00:31:51,159
But you just got custom suits last week.

550
00:31:51,243 --> 00:31:52,786
Why buy so many jackets again--

551
00:31:52,869 --> 00:31:54,663
Do you starve today
because you ate yesterday?

552
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:57,916
Don't get me wrong.
I appreciate the business.

553
00:31:57,999 --> 00:31:59,918
This will be my armor.

554
00:32:01,628 --> 00:32:04,464
I've got a battle coming up
that I refuse to lose.

555
00:32:04,548 --> 00:32:06,758
<i>When mating season arrives</i>
<i>in the animal kingdom,</i>

556
00:32:06,842 --> 00:32:09,636
<i>a fierce war of courtship begins.</i>

557
00:32:09,719 --> 00:32:12,806
<i>To seduce a female of their liking,</i>

558
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:14,850
<i>most males will shower</i>
<i>the females with gifts.</i>

559
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:19,062
<i>However, some animals seduce females</i>
<i>by showing off their flashy looks.</i>

560
00:32:19,146 --> 00:32:21,148
<i>The male peacock is one of them.</i>

561
00:32:21,857 --> 00:32:24,359
<i>He raises his tail feathers</i>
<i>to show off his beauty.</i>

562
00:32:24,443 --> 00:32:26,653
<i>Just look at him flap those wings.</i>

563
00:32:27,404 --> 00:32:31,491
<i>The peacock flaps its wings desperately</i>
<i>to avoid being left behind.</i>

564
00:32:32,617 --> 00:32:35,704
<i>In this courtship battle</i>
<i>for the female's favor,</i>

565
00:32:35,787 --> 00:32:39,291
<i>will this male emerge victorious?</i>

566
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,795
<i>The results will be revealed</i>
<i>in 60 seconds.</i>

567
00:32:53,138 --> 00:32:55,640
Mi-rae, what's the food truck
serving today?

568
00:32:56,433 --> 00:32:58,768
Darn it. It's spicy stir-fried pork again.

569
00:32:59,311 --> 00:33:00,979
- I like spicy pork.
- Sounds delicious.

570
00:33:03,857 --> 00:33:06,610
Look at Shin Seo-ri beaming and glowing.

571
00:33:06,693 --> 00:33:09,738
You even got a name this time.
"Court Lady Kim So-yun."

572
00:33:09,821 --> 00:33:11,615
Wow…

573
00:33:11,698 --> 00:33:14,326
You are that palace maid.
It has been a while.

574
00:33:14,409 --> 00:33:16,453
I see you have earned the right
to wear a <i>gache.</i>

575
00:33:16,536 --> 00:33:17,746
Oh right.

576
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:20,749
Yeah, I'm playing a minor court lady too.

577
00:33:21,583 --> 00:33:24,628
I heard you renewed your contract
and landed this role?

578
00:33:24,711 --> 00:33:26,463
How did you ever manage to win Hong over?

579
00:33:26,546 --> 00:33:28,840
She was totally ready
to terminate your contract before.

580
00:33:28,924 --> 00:33:30,091
Why the sudden renewal?

581
00:33:30,175 --> 00:33:32,010
Do not drag up old history.

582
00:33:32,093 --> 00:33:34,179
People ought to live looking ahead.

583
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:35,180
Excuse me.

584
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,852
She's got this weird aura now.

585
00:33:40,936 --> 00:33:41,895
GONG TAE-WOO'S SURPRISE ROMANCE

586
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:42,938
My poor head.

587
00:33:43,605 --> 00:33:45,273
- I'm about to get a cramp.
- Damn it.

588
00:33:45,357 --> 00:33:47,275
Hey, are we shooting Scene 36 today?

589
00:33:47,359 --> 00:33:48,610
<i>Gong Tae-woo.</i>

590
00:33:48,693 --> 00:33:51,488
<i>Do I really have to see</i>
<i>your cheating trending online?</i>

591
00:33:51,571 --> 00:33:53,990
<i>You'd better text back</i>
<i>while I'm still asking nicely.</i>

592
00:33:54,074 --> 00:33:56,618
Ji-hyo, wasn't she
your stand-in last time?

593
00:33:56,701 --> 00:33:57,869
The one who had the meltdown.

594
00:33:57,953 --> 00:33:59,204
Wait, isn't she Shin Seo-ri?

595
00:33:59,287 --> 00:34:01,873
The lead in that old drama, <i>Sonagi.</i>

596
00:34:01,957 --> 00:34:02,999
You're right.

597
00:34:03,083 --> 00:34:04,960
"The Nation's Pebble, Shin Seo-ri."

598
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:07,170
Ji-hyo, you made your acting debut
in that drama too.

599
00:34:07,254 --> 00:34:09,047
What? Ji-hyo was in that too?

600
00:34:09,130 --> 00:34:11,883
Yeah, she was
the class president in another class.

601
00:34:11,967 --> 00:34:14,010
The annoying girl who always
bullied the female lead--

602
00:34:14,094 --> 00:34:15,053
That's ancient history!

603
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:18,640
Have you forgotten the part
where her career tanked six months later

604
00:34:18,723 --> 00:34:19,683
because she can't act?

605
00:34:19,766 --> 00:34:20,934
Damn it.

606
00:34:21,476 --> 00:34:24,521
What the hell is she doing
with the assistant director anyway?

607
00:34:24,604 --> 00:34:27,232
Listen here.
Those two hanging around that minx.

608
00:34:27,315 --> 00:34:29,317
Are they supposed to be
Consorts Su-gui and So-yong?

609
00:34:29,401 --> 00:34:30,860
Excuse me? "Minx"?

610
00:34:31,486 --> 00:34:32,404
I mean Yoon Ji-hyo.

611
00:34:32,487 --> 00:34:35,323
I believe that minx is playing
the role of the Queen.

612
00:34:35,407 --> 00:34:37,200
Why does the Queen's hair look like that?

613
00:34:37,284 --> 00:34:39,911
And why are those underlings
wearing <i>gaches</i> en masse?

614
00:34:39,995 --> 00:34:42,038
- What about it?
- During King Anjong's reign,

615
00:34:42,122 --> 00:34:43,790
the ban on <i>gaches</i> was issued.

616
00:34:43,873 --> 00:34:44,749
So I ask you

617
00:34:44,833 --> 00:34:47,877
because those Inner Court minions
are all proudly wearing their <i>gaches.</i>

618
00:34:47,961 --> 00:34:48,878
Change them at once.

619
00:34:49,504 --> 00:34:52,007
I mean, who are you to demand
we make changes?

620
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:53,174
I mean…

621
00:34:54,175 --> 00:34:57,262
What are you doing here?
I told you to get the cinematographer.

622
00:34:57,345 --> 00:34:58,972
Well, this woman

623
00:34:59,055 --> 00:35:00,682
was spouting nonsense about the <i>gaches.</i>

624
00:35:00,765 --> 00:35:02,434
How dare you! "Nonsense"?

625
00:35:02,517 --> 00:35:06,438
Even if moral standards have hit
rock bottom in Hell Joseon,

626
00:35:06,521 --> 00:35:08,398
should we not at least strive
for historical accuracy?

627
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:09,566
Excuse me.

628
00:35:09,649 --> 00:35:11,860
You were the stand-in
for Royal Consort Jang last time, right?

629
00:35:11,943 --> 00:35:13,695
"Jang"? I am of the Kang clan!

630
00:35:13,778 --> 00:35:15,280
Look at that projection.

631
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:16,448
Great commanding tone.

632
00:35:16,531 --> 00:35:18,199
Thanks to that commanding tone,

633
00:35:18,283 --> 00:35:20,035
our drama shorts got a lot of buzz.

634
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:22,746
But that one viral moment has got you
way too committed to the bit.

635
00:35:22,829 --> 00:35:25,248
You're in too deep. You can't do that.

636
00:35:25,332 --> 00:35:26,875
Are you the chief here?

637
00:35:26,958 --> 00:35:28,460
Right, I'm the chief…

638
00:35:29,085 --> 00:35:29,961
"Chief"?

639
00:35:30,045 --> 00:35:32,213
I have been utterly unable
to reason with this dunce.

640
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:34,257
Your presence is most welcome.

641
00:35:34,341 --> 00:35:37,260
Let us go somewhere quiet
and have a frank discussion.

642
00:35:38,094 --> 00:35:41,056
Director, what's going on?

643
00:35:41,139 --> 00:35:43,600
Ji-hyo. She's an actor
from your agency, right?

644
00:35:44,225 --> 00:35:46,394
Where is Ms. Hong? Go get Ms. Hong.

645
00:35:46,478 --> 00:35:48,730
She needs to keep her actors in check.
This is unacceptable.

646
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:52,400
Oh my, did Seo-ri already make
some sort of mistake?

647
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:53,568
I'm so sorry.

648
00:35:53,652 --> 00:35:55,362
I know we're from the same agency,

649
00:35:55,445 --> 00:35:58,365
but I did warn them
against pulling strings for her.

650
00:35:58,448 --> 00:36:00,742
I'm mortified as the lead of this drama.

651
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:02,035
As if.

652
00:36:02,118 --> 00:36:03,203
This is why

653
00:36:03,286 --> 00:36:05,455
I say you can't fix up
an old, washed-up rookie.

654
00:36:05,538 --> 00:36:07,374
Didn't I, you dunce?
You cast her, didn't you?

655
00:36:07,457 --> 00:36:08,667
She must be a favor hire.

656
00:36:08,750 --> 00:36:10,585
Jeez. No wonder.

657
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:13,880
<i>These wretches dare to publicly shame me</i>

658
00:36:13,963 --> 00:36:16,383
<i>to my very face.</i>

659
00:36:18,176 --> 00:36:20,261
Listen, since Ji-hyo
is speaking up for you,

660
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:21,513
I'll let it slide this once.

661
00:36:21,596 --> 00:36:23,264
But there won't be a second time.

662
00:36:23,348 --> 00:36:24,599
You should offer her a deep bow.

663
00:36:24,683 --> 00:36:26,393
- What?
- No need.

664
00:36:26,476 --> 00:36:28,728
It's fine, Director. Please calm down.

665
00:36:28,812 --> 00:36:31,648
The crew is working so hard.

666
00:36:31,731 --> 00:36:35,068
Let me treat everyone to iced Americanos
to celebrate the start of Season 2.

667
00:36:35,151 --> 00:36:36,653
Let's get back to it.

668
00:36:36,736 --> 00:36:38,863
- Look here, Chief.
- She's not a favor hire.

669
00:36:38,947 --> 00:36:41,950
- "Chief"? Did she really call me that?
- Come on, Director.

670
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:45,120
What's her name again? Seo-ri?

671
00:36:53,837 --> 00:36:56,131
Cut! Okay, next scene!

672
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:01,594
Great work, everyone.

673
00:37:03,304 --> 00:37:05,849
Look at that minx asserting her dominion

674
00:37:05,932 --> 00:37:07,350
and marking her territory.

675
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:10,603
It is both infuriating and grating.

676
00:37:10,687 --> 00:37:13,064
Swiftly rising to distinction
is my only option.

677
00:37:13,898 --> 00:37:15,608
Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

678
00:37:15,692 --> 00:37:17,527
- Thanks for the latte.
- Thank you.

679
00:37:17,610 --> 00:37:19,988
- Good luck, Seo-ri.
- Thanks for the drink.

680
00:37:20,071 --> 00:37:21,656
- Thanks for the drink.
- Thank you.

681
00:37:21,740 --> 00:37:23,742
- Thank you.
- Thanks for the treat.

682
00:37:24,492 --> 00:37:25,410
What the…

683
00:37:26,035 --> 00:37:28,496
Why are they suddenly being so nice?

684
00:37:36,671 --> 00:37:39,966
<i>The number you have dialed is unavailable.</i>
<i>You will be transferred to voicemail…</i>

685
00:37:40,049 --> 00:37:41,926
Now he's blocked me?

686
00:37:42,469 --> 00:37:44,596
That scumbag. Damn it.

687
00:37:47,307 --> 00:37:48,725
Go get me an iced Americano.

688
00:37:48,808 --> 00:37:50,310
- Overflowing with ice.
- Okay.

689
00:37:50,393 --> 00:37:52,729
Yes, sure. Thank you.

690
00:37:52,812 --> 00:37:54,773
Hey, the delivery is going to be delayed

691
00:37:54,856 --> 00:37:56,316
because it's lunchtime.

692
00:37:56,900 --> 00:37:58,818
- Isn't that what you ordered?
- What?

693
00:37:58,902 --> 00:38:00,403
Someone else sent a coffee truck?

694
00:38:00,487 --> 00:38:03,281
I'll cancel our order right away.

695
00:38:03,865 --> 00:38:04,908
Really?

696
00:38:04,991 --> 00:38:07,577
The lead should kick it off.
Who could be this thoughtless?

697
00:38:09,245 --> 00:38:10,830
Wait. Hold on a second.

698
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:14,834
"Courtesy of Shin Seo-ri,
the acting virtuoso"?

699
00:38:14,918 --> 00:38:15,794
Ji-hyo.

700
00:38:17,712 --> 00:38:20,131
Did Shin Seo-ri send a coffee truck?

701
00:38:20,215 --> 00:38:22,217
COURTESY OF SHIN SEO-RI
THE ACTING VIRTUOSO

702
00:38:22,634 --> 00:38:23,593
SHIN SEO-RI'S QUEENDOM OF BEAUTY

703
00:38:28,431 --> 00:38:30,600
- This is me. Right here.
- Seo-ri, you look beautiful.

704
00:38:30,683 --> 00:38:32,143
Please look over here.

705
00:38:32,227 --> 00:38:34,479
You're so pretty. I'm a fan.

706
00:38:38,858 --> 00:38:40,235
- Could I get a picture?
- Sure.

707
00:38:44,739 --> 00:38:45,698
Thank you.

708
00:38:45,782 --> 00:38:48,117
Thank you, Seo-ri. Thanks for the treat.

709
00:38:48,743 --> 00:38:51,663
- Thanks for the treat.
- Thank you, everyone.

710
00:38:52,914 --> 00:38:54,207
In my entire life,

711
00:38:54,290 --> 00:38:57,710
I have never before received
gratitude from such a horde at once.

712
00:38:57,794 --> 00:39:00,421
It is a hundred times better
than being treated like dirt.

713
00:39:00,505 --> 00:39:02,048
Seo-ri, you're so pretty.

714
00:39:02,966 --> 00:39:04,342
I am Shin Seo-ri.

715
00:39:04,884 --> 00:39:06,135
I am <i>the </i>Shin Seo-ri.

716
00:39:07,971 --> 00:39:09,681
Now, smile.

717
00:39:12,225 --> 00:39:13,935
How does it feel, Shin Seo-ri?

718
00:39:16,479 --> 00:39:18,648
Are you finally feeling
that tsunami of emotion?

719
00:39:18,731 --> 00:39:19,816
Cha Se-gye?

720
00:39:20,733 --> 00:39:21,860
Don't say my name out loud.

721
00:39:21,943 --> 00:39:22,986
Wait…

722
00:39:24,237 --> 00:39:26,114
Was this all your doing, Cha Se-gye?

723
00:39:26,197 --> 00:39:28,157
Seriously? I just told you
to stop saying my name.

724
00:39:28,241 --> 00:39:29,200
You scoundrel.

725
00:39:29,284 --> 00:39:30,285
Ms. Hong.

726
00:39:30,368 --> 00:39:33,121
You paired Shin Seo-ri up with me
without saying anything,

727
00:39:33,204 --> 00:39:34,914
and now you're even sending coffee trucks?

728
00:39:34,998 --> 00:39:37,667
Have you ever seen me waste my money?

729
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,460
There's a proper order to everything.

730
00:39:39,544 --> 00:39:42,130
Why would I get one for <i>her</i> first?

731
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:46,384
Hold on. So it really wasn't you?

732
00:39:46,467 --> 00:39:47,677
- No.
- Then,

733
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,929
who the hell wasted their money on that?

734
00:39:50,013 --> 00:39:52,765
Maybe a fan sent it.

735
00:39:52,849 --> 00:39:54,726
Since when does she have fans?

736
00:39:58,396 --> 00:39:59,314
Damn it.

737
00:40:00,648 --> 00:40:01,941
I mean…

738
00:40:04,652 --> 00:40:05,987
What are you plotting now?

739
00:40:06,070 --> 00:40:08,573
What scheme are you hatching
that requires such bribery?

740
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:11,910
I suppose you could call it a bribe.

741
00:40:11,993 --> 00:40:13,077
There is an ulterior motive.

742
00:40:13,161 --> 00:40:14,537
"Ulterior motive"?

743
00:40:14,621 --> 00:40:16,789
Now you are finally showing
your true colors.

744
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:19,834
You are not a fan or an ally,
yet you pretended to care.

745
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:21,836
What is your ulterior motive?

746
00:40:28,009 --> 00:40:30,678
As of today,
I'm officially setting this as my target.

747
00:40:31,679 --> 00:40:33,056
My heart.

748
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:35,141
What are you going to do to it?

749
00:40:35,224 --> 00:40:37,268
Yeah. I'm going to steal your heart.

750
00:40:38,770 --> 00:40:39,854
You said you felt nothing.

751
00:40:39,938 --> 00:40:41,564
That I moved you less than a stray mutt.

752
00:40:41,648 --> 00:40:43,691
I haven't slept for days after that.

753
00:40:43,775 --> 00:40:44,859
It got to me.

754
00:40:44,943 --> 00:40:48,404
Whether you sleep or do handstands,
what does that have to do with me?

755
00:40:48,488 --> 00:40:50,031
Look at you, acting tough again.

756
00:40:50,114 --> 00:40:53,034
The thing is,
I realized I overlooked something.

757
00:40:53,618 --> 00:40:54,535
And what is that?

758
00:40:54,619 --> 00:40:57,789
That a woman like you, Shin Seo-ri,
is far from innocent.

759
00:40:58,915 --> 00:41:01,167
Are you saying I am dirty and vulgar?

760
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:02,502
You're a skilled liar.

761
00:41:03,127 --> 00:41:05,672
You'll use any means necessary
to achieve your goals.

762
00:41:05,755 --> 00:41:07,757
In short, you're a dangerous woman.

763
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:11,052
<i>So are you going to be petty now</i>

764
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:13,554
<i>and suggest we cancel our contract?</i>

765
00:41:13,638 --> 00:41:15,181
But the thing is,

766
00:41:15,264 --> 00:41:16,933
I've never been one to lose.

767
00:41:17,016 --> 00:41:19,352
So I'm confident
I won't lose this time either.

768
00:41:20,979 --> 00:41:22,188
<i>Maybe not?</i>

769
00:41:22,271 --> 00:41:23,982
<i>Is he looking for a fight?</i>

770
00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:27,318
- Is this retaliation?
- No, it's a surrender.

771
00:41:28,778 --> 00:41:31,656
They say in love and war,
sometimes losing is winning.

772
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:36,661
<i>What is with this intense stare?</i>

773
00:41:36,744 --> 00:41:39,038
Look, I admit I skipped
the romantic gestures

774
00:41:39,122 --> 00:41:40,790
and acted a bit rashly.

775
00:41:41,624 --> 00:41:45,294
So let's wipe the slate clean

776
00:41:45,378 --> 00:41:46,421
and start over.

777
00:41:46,504 --> 00:41:49,298
<i>What is with this duplicity?</i>

778
00:41:49,382 --> 00:41:51,342
<i>Cold and ruthless to the core,</i>

779
00:41:51,426 --> 00:41:53,636
<i>yet those eyes are nothing but sincere.</i>

780
00:41:54,262 --> 00:41:55,471
<i>Could he be…</i>

781
00:41:56,472 --> 00:42:00,268
Do you… truly harbor affection for me?

782
00:42:00,893 --> 00:42:01,769
I do.

783
00:42:08,609 --> 00:42:12,613
<i>Why is this fool</i>
<i>charging in headfirst like this?</i>

784
00:42:23,833 --> 00:42:26,085
I get it. You're a woman,

785
00:42:26,169 --> 00:42:28,629
so accepting right away
would hurt your pride.

786
00:42:29,797 --> 00:42:31,883
I'll give you a day to protect your ego.

787
00:42:31,966 --> 00:42:33,426
No need.

788
00:42:33,509 --> 00:42:34,677
Here is my definitive answer.

789
00:42:36,888 --> 00:42:38,848
It has never changed,
and I guarantee it never will.

790
00:42:38,931 --> 00:42:39,974
Cha Se-gye.

791
00:42:40,058 --> 00:42:41,601
I harbor

792
00:42:41,684 --> 00:42:42,852
no affection for you.

793
00:42:44,020 --> 00:42:46,522
Not now, not ever, until the end of time.

794
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:57,075
Oh my.

795
00:43:01,496 --> 00:43:03,623
That wicked degenerate.

796
00:43:03,706 --> 00:43:05,875
Launching a surprise attack
in close combat.

797
00:43:07,293 --> 00:43:08,711
I am a Buddhist nun.

798
00:43:08,795 --> 00:43:10,296
A Buddhist nun with long hair.

799
00:43:25,103 --> 00:43:26,187
Hey, Shin Seo-ri.

800
00:43:26,854 --> 00:43:28,898
You take this.
The smell is giving me a headache.

801
00:43:28,981 --> 00:43:30,024
You…

802
00:43:32,401 --> 00:43:33,444
Did you buy flowers too?

803
00:43:33,528 --> 00:43:35,321
Don't read into it. It's annoying.

804
00:43:47,083 --> 00:43:48,000
What's that about?

805
00:43:51,504 --> 00:43:53,381
That's a supercar.

806
00:43:54,382 --> 00:43:56,592
Shin Seo-ri, that loser, has a boyfriend?

807
00:44:10,898 --> 00:44:12,441
You dare reject me?

808
00:44:12,525 --> 00:44:14,861
Not just once, but twice?

809
00:44:20,032 --> 00:44:22,034
CHIEF OF STAFF SON JAE-HAN

810
00:44:22,368 --> 00:44:23,828
<i>Sir, you're on your way, right?</i>

811
00:44:23,911 --> 00:44:26,164
Today is the dinner
at the Chairman's estate.

812
00:44:26,247 --> 00:44:28,040
- Did you perhaps forget--
<i>- Do you have any idea</i>

813
00:44:28,124 --> 00:44:31,210
the humiliation I just suffered
because of you, Mr. Son?

814
00:44:31,294 --> 00:44:32,837
Wait, what did I do--

815
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:35,715
That's on me for asking
a cat-cuddling old bachelor.

816
00:44:52,982 --> 00:44:54,233
Damn it.

817
00:44:54,317 --> 00:44:56,986
Oh my, I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

818
00:44:57,653 --> 00:45:00,448
- It's you, right?
- What?

819
00:45:01,616 --> 00:45:03,451
Earlier at the shop.

820
00:45:04,160 --> 00:45:05,036
Don't you remember?

821
00:45:05,119 --> 00:45:07,079
Shop? What shop?

822
00:45:07,163 --> 00:45:08,039
Have we met?

823
00:45:08,122 --> 00:45:09,582
The coffee at the tailor shop.

824
00:45:09,665 --> 00:45:11,417
I spilled coffee on you.

825
00:45:11,500 --> 00:45:12,960
Right, that coffee.

826
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:16,297
You seem to be quite accident-prone.

827
00:45:16,923 --> 00:45:19,634
I don't think my face is that forgettable.

828
00:45:22,261 --> 00:45:24,222
Don't say no a second time. Call me.

829
00:45:24,305 --> 00:45:27,141
Aftereffects of a car accident
are what get you.

830
00:45:31,812 --> 00:45:34,440
- "Trinice"?
- It's my company.

831
00:45:34,523 --> 00:45:37,610
I've got enough money not to hit
someone's car and just drive off,

832
00:45:37,693 --> 00:45:40,571
so make sure to bill me
for your treatment.

833
00:45:53,084 --> 00:45:55,336
An epic clash
of relentlessly stubborn titans.

834
00:45:55,419 --> 00:45:58,673
Is this the age-old battle
of spear versus shield?

835
00:45:58,756 --> 00:46:01,384
Weren't you the one who told me
to stop going on blind dates?

836
00:46:01,467 --> 00:46:05,596
I've already struck out in that world
and been blacklisted there.

837
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,306
You may have struck out domestically,

838
00:46:07,390 --> 00:46:10,268
but the overseas market
remains an untapped goldmine.

839
00:46:10,351 --> 00:46:12,645
Counter twisted logic
by twisting your own.

840
00:46:12,728 --> 00:46:14,021
Does scrap metal turn into silver

841
00:46:14,105 --> 00:46:16,524
just by crossing an ocean, Grandfather?

842
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:19,068
Stop complaining and make time this week.

843
00:46:19,151 --> 00:46:21,570
I don't even mind
if she can't speak Korean well.

844
00:46:22,363 --> 00:46:23,447
Utilize false reasoning

845
00:46:23,531 --> 00:46:26,242
and distortion to force
the desired conclusion.

846
00:46:28,035 --> 00:46:29,912
I really don't have the time.

847
00:46:35,835 --> 00:46:38,421
Grandfather, are you trying
to pull a ruse?

848
00:46:41,173 --> 00:46:43,175
I almost fell for it.

849
00:46:45,177 --> 00:46:46,512
Sharp-eyed devil.

850
00:46:46,595 --> 00:46:49,640
You were so hopeless at blind dates.

851
00:46:49,724 --> 00:46:52,810
I figured you were more
of an organic meeting type.

852
00:46:52,893 --> 00:46:54,186
Was that so terrible of me?

853
00:46:54,270 --> 00:46:55,646
"Organic." How hip.

854
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:58,107
If she's willing to play along
with this ridiculous act,

855
00:46:58,190 --> 00:46:59,442
it's obvious what she's like.

856
00:46:59,525 --> 00:47:01,193
Either naive or stupid.

857
00:47:01,277 --> 00:47:03,654
She's a smart young lady
who's perfect for you.

858
00:47:03,738 --> 00:47:05,489
That's why I changed my mind.

859
00:47:05,573 --> 00:47:07,241
You must have met her first.

860
00:47:07,325 --> 00:47:08,993
If she's that great, you should marry her.

861
00:47:09,076 --> 00:47:10,661
What? You rotten punk!

862
00:47:10,745 --> 00:47:13,205
When you're outmatched,
go for the jugular.

863
00:47:13,289 --> 00:47:14,957
A foolproof strategy for victory.

864
00:47:35,895 --> 00:47:37,104
I do.

865
00:47:41,275 --> 00:47:42,443
Jeez.

866
00:47:49,367 --> 00:47:53,496
Did he really think some common flowers
would sway me in the slightest?

867
00:47:55,081 --> 00:47:56,999
My welfare is my first priority.

868
00:47:57,083 --> 00:47:58,584
And my second.

869
00:48:00,002 --> 00:48:02,671
In this life,
I will be sure to guard my heart

870
00:48:03,839 --> 00:48:05,925
and live out my days to the fullest.

871
00:48:18,646 --> 00:48:20,064
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

872
00:48:23,442 --> 00:48:25,403
Your Highness, what brings you here?

873
00:48:25,486 --> 00:48:27,029
These are my secret quarters.

874
00:48:27,113 --> 00:48:28,656
What are you doing here?

875
00:48:29,907 --> 00:48:31,075
I was just…

876
00:48:40,543 --> 00:48:41,752
What are you burying?

877
00:48:42,378 --> 00:48:44,630
Did you bury a stolen trinket?

878
00:48:45,923 --> 00:48:48,217
I did not steal anything.

879
00:48:49,135 --> 00:48:51,262
Do you take me for some petty thief?

880
00:48:51,804 --> 00:48:54,140
There, the spark is back in your eyes.

881
00:48:54,223 --> 00:48:56,308
Do not sulk like some mutt
caught in the rain.

882
00:48:56,392 --> 00:48:58,519
You are only yourself when you are feisty.

883
00:48:59,562 --> 00:49:01,272
Speaking of,

884
00:49:01,355 --> 00:49:04,066
where did that mutt go?

885
00:49:07,611 --> 00:49:09,530
Did you chase it away?

886
00:49:18,664 --> 00:49:21,417
Or… is it dead?

887
00:49:25,463 --> 00:49:27,173
It died.

888
00:49:29,758 --> 00:49:31,886
I killed it.

889
00:49:35,181 --> 00:49:36,557
That cannot be true.

890
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:38,267
If you had indeed killed it,

891
00:49:38,350 --> 00:49:41,687
you would not be looking so distraught,
making a grave for it.

892
00:49:51,947 --> 00:49:53,824
Let us at least pray

893
00:49:53,908 --> 00:49:56,035
for this nameless dog's soul.

894
00:49:57,453 --> 00:49:59,455
So that it may find peace
in the afterlife.

895
00:50:02,791 --> 00:50:03,834
May you

896
00:50:04,877 --> 00:50:08,672
be reborn as a human in your next life
and live out your days to the fullest.

897
00:50:16,055 --> 00:50:18,349
May you live out your days to the fullest.

898
00:51:21,412 --> 00:51:23,372
Why did he have to give me these?

899
00:51:25,874 --> 00:51:29,128
But they are still living things.
I cannot just throw them away.

900
00:51:29,211 --> 00:51:30,921
It'd be a waste to toss out flowers.

901
00:51:31,005 --> 00:51:32,256
Someone must've asked her out.

902
00:51:32,339 --> 00:51:34,508
Did Unit 204 give it to you?

903
00:51:34,592 --> 00:51:35,467
Be quiet.

904
00:51:35,551 --> 00:51:37,303
Enough chattering.
Hang your laundry and go.

905
00:51:38,345 --> 00:51:40,264
Jeez. What's with the attitude?

906
00:51:42,975 --> 00:51:44,643
Did you watch
<i>The Women's Kingdom</i> yesterday?

907
00:51:44,727 --> 00:51:47,187
I can't believe Season 2 started.

908
00:51:47,271 --> 00:51:48,689
Yoon Ji-hyo got even prettier.

909
00:51:48,772 --> 00:51:51,483
- Her skin is flawless.
- She must spend a fortune on it.

910
00:51:51,567 --> 00:51:53,861
That minx's glowing skin

911
00:51:53,944 --> 00:51:55,613
is just caked-on makeup.

912
00:51:56,280 --> 00:51:58,657
What the… You tell us
to be quiet, then chime in?

913
00:51:58,741 --> 00:52:00,409
She's just dissing her out of jealousy.

914
00:52:00,492 --> 00:52:01,577
As if she's ever seen her.

915
00:52:01,660 --> 00:52:03,704
Of course I have. I saw her yesterday.

916
00:52:03,787 --> 00:52:04,830
Where?

917
00:52:05,456 --> 00:52:07,958
Probably at her part-time gig.

918
00:52:08,042 --> 00:52:09,710
Rooftop is an actor too. A wannabe.

919
00:52:09,793 --> 00:52:12,630
- Stop lying.
- It's true. She goes to film sets.

920
00:52:12,713 --> 00:52:14,256
You think just anyone can be an actor?

921
00:52:14,340 --> 00:52:15,591
Those brats.

922
00:52:15,674 --> 00:52:18,844
I give them my yard for their laundry
and get zero gratitude.

923
00:52:19,720 --> 00:52:20,721
Damn it.

924
00:52:22,848 --> 00:52:25,934
This is why you should never
carelessly let someone in.

925
00:52:33,275 --> 00:52:34,568
<i>I'll be sending the schedule</i>

926
00:52:34,652 --> 00:52:37,154
for the Jeju Island shoot in two days,
so pack your bags.

927
00:52:37,237 --> 00:52:40,824
Ji-hyo is on vacation, so I'll let you use
her van and road manager for now.

928
00:52:40,908 --> 00:52:41,992
<i>Take advantage of that.</i>

929
00:52:42,076 --> 00:52:44,536
I refuse anything that belongs
to that minx.

930
00:52:44,620 --> 00:52:47,247
I shall carefully handpick my own person,

931
00:52:47,331 --> 00:52:48,624
so be aware.

932
00:52:53,837 --> 00:52:55,255
Can't sleep lately?

933
00:52:55,339 --> 00:52:58,967
Every time I lie down,
I get so mad that I can't fall asleep.

934
00:52:59,051 --> 00:53:01,261
Lying in bed and suddenly cringing
at the past is normal.

935
00:53:01,345 --> 00:53:02,971
Turn off your brain. Maybe meditate.

936
00:53:03,055 --> 00:53:04,848
How can I turn it off?

937
00:53:04,932 --> 00:53:06,517
I've never been so insulted in my life.

938
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:07,935
Yeah, the news comments are nuts,

939
00:53:08,018 --> 00:53:09,937
cursing you out
and calling you a corporate raider.

940
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:13,190
I can't just let this go.
It's too humiliating.

941
00:53:15,192 --> 00:53:16,151
I need revenge.

942
00:53:17,403 --> 00:53:19,154
"Revenge"?

943
00:53:19,697 --> 00:53:21,949
A fresh scandal always drowns out
the last one.

944
00:53:22,032 --> 00:53:24,785
Just be patient.
Time will solve everything.

945
00:53:24,868 --> 00:53:26,412
"Fresh scandal"?

946
00:53:28,455 --> 00:53:29,581
Yeah.

947
00:53:30,416 --> 00:53:32,292
That's a good way to bury it.

948
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:34,628
Thanks for the session today.

949
00:53:34,712 --> 00:53:36,630
You've become a real miracle worker.

950
00:53:37,631 --> 00:53:39,049
Hey, don't forget your meds!

951
00:53:42,511 --> 00:53:45,639
Nurse Kim, could you take this
to Mr. Cha Se-gye?

952
00:53:45,723 --> 00:53:47,474
Sure, give it to me.

953
00:53:49,768 --> 00:53:51,019
Mr. Son.

954
00:53:51,103 --> 00:53:52,396
Call Grandfather.

955
00:53:52,938 --> 00:53:55,232
Tell him I'll go on that blind date
as soon as possible.

956
00:53:55,315 --> 00:53:57,735
Mr. Cha Se-gye, your medication is ready.

957
00:54:00,279 --> 00:54:02,906
No, just stop talking and do it now.

958
00:54:02,990 --> 00:54:03,991
HANBIT MENTAL HEALTH CLINIC

959
00:54:07,244 --> 00:54:09,371
DELIVERY COMPLETED

960
00:54:17,713 --> 00:54:20,090
"In the Anglo-American legal system,

961
00:54:20,632 --> 00:54:24,678
police are formed as an organization
granted autonomous authority by citizens…"

962
00:54:24,762 --> 00:54:25,679
Is that good?

963
00:54:25,763 --> 00:54:26,972
Jesus!

964
00:54:27,765 --> 00:54:30,809
Make some noise when you walk.
You're not a ghost.

965
00:54:37,983 --> 00:54:40,611
<i>Your physique may be lacking,</i>

966
00:54:40,694 --> 00:54:42,780
<i>but you survive on noodles day after day</i>

967
00:54:42,863 --> 00:54:45,240
<i>and remain a penny-pincher.</i>

968
00:54:45,324 --> 00:54:47,201
<i>Your survival skills are top-notch.</i>

969
00:54:50,329 --> 00:54:51,205
What's up?

970
00:54:52,539 --> 00:54:56,001
<i>And despite all my scolding,</i>
<i>you still talk back to me.</i>

971
00:54:56,627 --> 00:54:58,504
<i>You are more tenacious than you look.</i>

972
00:55:00,464 --> 00:55:03,383
Will you place yourself in my service?

973
00:55:03,467 --> 00:55:04,635
What are you talking about?

974
00:55:04,718 --> 00:55:05,844
I shall

975
00:55:05,928 --> 00:55:08,555
personally appoint you as my "nodo."

976
00:55:08,639 --> 00:55:10,390
"Nodo"? What's that?

977
00:55:10,474 --> 00:55:12,434
"No" as in "toil." "Do" as in "guide."

978
00:55:12,518 --> 00:55:13,894
"To guide through toil."

979
00:55:13,977 --> 00:55:16,146
Have you never heard of a "nodo" manager?

980
00:55:16,230 --> 00:55:17,272
"Nodo"?

981
00:55:19,817 --> 00:55:20,984
I see.

982
00:55:21,068 --> 00:55:23,320
You mean "road manager"?

983
00:55:25,531 --> 00:55:27,157
You think I've been working part-time gigs

984
00:55:27,241 --> 00:55:29,034
day and night just to become your driver?

985
00:55:29,117 --> 00:55:30,327
I'll have you know,

986
00:55:30,410 --> 00:55:32,913
I graduated
from a four-year university in Seoul.

987
00:55:32,996 --> 00:55:36,416
So you even possess some knowledge.
You are a perfect fit.

988
00:55:36,500 --> 00:55:39,002
My standards for choosing subordinates
are quite strict,

989
00:55:39,086 --> 00:55:41,296
but no matter how I look at it,

990
00:55:41,380 --> 00:55:42,798
there is no talent quite like you.

991
00:55:42,881 --> 00:55:44,591
Are you even listening to me?

992
00:55:44,675 --> 00:55:45,926
Even if I'm desperate for money,

993
00:55:46,009 --> 00:55:48,554
I'd never be crazy enough to work for you.

994
00:55:48,637 --> 00:55:50,180
How much would satisfy you?

995
00:55:50,264 --> 00:55:51,849
I will pay whatever you ask.

996
00:55:51,932 --> 00:55:54,142
Pay whatever I ask?
You live in a rooftop room.

997
00:55:54,226 --> 00:55:55,727
Three times your minimum wage.

998
00:55:56,937 --> 00:55:59,064
Would three times satisfy you?

999
00:56:01,900 --> 00:56:03,986
You think you can just buy me with money?

1000
00:56:04,069 --> 00:56:05,237
I won't do it! No way!

1001
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:06,321
Damn it.

1002
00:56:06,822 --> 00:56:08,532
I screwed up. Royally screwed up.

1003
00:56:09,283 --> 00:56:10,826
Damn my need for money.

1004
00:56:10,909 --> 00:56:13,579
She offered triple the pay.
How could I refuse that?

1005
00:56:13,662 --> 00:56:16,707
What are you doing? Move yourself quickly!

1006
00:56:17,958 --> 00:56:19,668
Have you never been to Jeju?

1007
00:56:19,751 --> 00:56:21,044
Why are you so dressed up?

1008
00:56:21,128 --> 00:56:22,880
And what's with the weird glasses?

1009
00:56:22,963 --> 00:56:24,464
As a celebrity,

1010
00:56:24,548 --> 00:56:28,010
one must never let one's guard down,
even at departure.

1011
00:56:28,552 --> 00:56:30,345
Are the reporters not here yet?

1012
00:56:31,013 --> 00:56:32,014
"Departure"?

1013
00:56:32,097 --> 00:56:34,641
By the way, I saw online
that the CEO of the company

1014
00:56:34,725 --> 00:56:36,351
you're shooting the commercial for

1015
00:56:36,435 --> 00:56:39,354
is getting a ton of hate for being
morally corrupt and controversial.

1016
00:56:39,438 --> 00:56:41,315
- You sure about this?
- What does it matter?

1017
00:56:41,398 --> 00:56:43,108
As long as we are making money.

1018
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:46,862
Then again, that would be the pot
calling the kettle black. Who's to judge?

1019
00:56:46,945 --> 00:56:48,071
Why, you…

1020
00:56:50,324 --> 00:56:53,911
There's absolutely no need for the CEO
to be there for a campaign shoot.

1021
00:56:54,578 --> 00:56:57,623
Out of all our marketing strategies,
isn't this ad the top priority right now?

1022
00:56:57,706 --> 00:57:01,209
The advertiser <i>should</i> be there on set,
overseeing things directly.

1023
00:57:03,253 --> 00:57:05,964
I was hoping to sneak in
some long-overdue PTO on this work trip.

1024
00:57:06,048 --> 00:57:07,090
Guess not.

1025
00:57:09,092 --> 00:57:11,678
Welcome aboard. Have a pleasant flight.

1026
00:57:12,304 --> 00:57:13,680
Welcome aboard.

1027
00:57:15,515 --> 00:57:17,517
If you live long enough,
you really do see it all.

1028
00:57:17,601 --> 00:57:20,520
A marvel to fly through the skies
while still very much alive.

1029
00:57:22,064 --> 00:57:23,523
This will do.

1030
00:57:25,776 --> 00:57:27,653
The seats are so plush.

1031
00:57:27,736 --> 00:57:29,863
I can sleep with both legs stretched out.

1032
00:57:30,489 --> 00:57:32,658
Why do you walk so fast?

1033
00:57:32,741 --> 00:57:33,784
I told you to wait for me.

1034
00:57:33,867 --> 00:57:35,577
It is your feet that are slow.

1035
00:57:35,661 --> 00:57:37,913
I have saved us good seats.
Sit down quickly.

1036
00:57:37,996 --> 00:57:39,331
What?

1037
00:57:39,414 --> 00:57:41,375
These aren't our seats. Get up.

1038
00:57:41,458 --> 00:57:43,961
They are not?
Then where are our seats?

1039
00:57:44,044 --> 00:57:45,003
Come on. Let's go.

1040
00:57:49,257 --> 00:57:51,176
Those seats over there
were nice and roomy.

1041
00:57:51,259 --> 00:57:52,427
Why is it so cramped here?

1042
00:57:52,511 --> 00:57:54,179
Because that was business class.

1043
00:57:54,262 --> 00:57:55,597
This is economy.

1044
00:57:55,681 --> 00:57:57,975
You could've just paid extra
if you liked it that much.

1045
00:57:58,058 --> 00:57:59,977
So they divide the seats based on money?

1046
00:58:00,686 --> 00:58:01,979
Is that what you are saying?

1047
00:58:02,062 --> 00:58:03,271
This wretched Hell Joseon.

1048
00:58:03,355 --> 00:58:04,523
Let's keep it moving.

1049
00:58:04,606 --> 00:58:06,483
- Sorry.
- What are they even doing?

1050
00:58:06,566 --> 00:58:09,111
- Hurry up and sit down. Just sit.
- So cramped.

1051
00:58:09,861 --> 00:58:10,737
Miserable bastards.

1052
00:58:10,821 --> 00:58:12,572
Why not make it clear from the start?

1053
00:58:12,656 --> 00:58:14,157
Beggars, commoners, and noblemen.

1054
00:58:14,241 --> 00:58:15,951
They might as well label the sections.

1055
00:58:16,034 --> 00:58:20,580
Listen, I've been meaning to
ask you something for a while now.

1056
00:58:20,664 --> 00:58:23,250
Did you actually finish
your compulsory education?

1057
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:26,336
Because your English seems a bit lacking.

1058
00:58:27,212 --> 00:58:29,089
I am fluent in the language
of the mainland.

1059
00:58:29,172 --> 00:58:31,341
I have mastered
both the <i>Sohak </i>and the <i>Analects.</i>

1060
00:58:32,092 --> 00:58:34,386
Right. So your English is lacking.

1061
00:58:45,272 --> 00:58:46,565
Sir,

1062
00:58:46,648 --> 00:58:49,026
your recent insomnia
is work-related, right?

1063
00:58:49,109 --> 00:58:50,861
Or maybe something shifted personally?

1064
00:58:50,944 --> 00:58:52,237
Why?

1065
00:58:52,320 --> 00:58:54,614
Did Grandfather call you in
and grill you again?

1066
00:58:54,698 --> 00:58:57,367
No, sir. Nothing like that happened.

1067
00:58:57,451 --> 00:58:58,869
You won't be grilled anymore.

1068
00:58:58,952 --> 00:59:00,912
I decided to grant his wish, remember?

1069
00:59:00,996 --> 00:59:03,290
Why did you suddenly change your mind?

1070
00:59:03,373 --> 00:59:04,499
You said you were too busy.

1071
00:59:04,583 --> 00:59:06,460
Well, I found a need
for it myself as well.

1072
00:59:06,543 --> 00:59:07,919
It's a win-win situation.

1073
00:59:08,545 --> 00:59:10,839
It's a bit hot in here, though.

1074
00:59:12,632 --> 00:59:13,675
Is it just me?

1075
00:59:19,890 --> 00:59:21,391
I need to move around a bit.

1076
00:59:22,476 --> 00:59:23,351
Excuse me.

1077
00:59:24,144 --> 00:59:26,354
- Could he get a glass of cold water?
- Right away.

1078
00:59:31,193 --> 00:59:32,360
Goodness.

1079
00:59:33,695 --> 00:59:35,113
Jeez.

1080
00:59:35,739 --> 00:59:38,658
Please just sit still.
The person in front is staring.

1081
00:59:38,742 --> 00:59:41,578
It feels like I paid money to be tortured.

1082
00:59:41,661 --> 00:59:43,246
I would rather have my legs twisted.

1083
00:59:43,330 --> 00:59:45,123
Did you only ever fly business class?

1084
00:59:45,207 --> 00:59:46,666
Just hang in there.

1085
00:59:46,750 --> 00:59:49,044
I'm going to use the restroom.

1086
00:59:49,795 --> 00:59:51,088
Shoot!

1087
00:59:51,171 --> 00:59:53,465
You scoundrel! You wretched scoundrel!

1088
00:59:53,548 --> 00:59:55,175
Pardon me. Sorry.

1089
00:59:55,801 --> 00:59:57,969
I was thrilled to fly through the skies,

1090
00:59:58,053 --> 01:00:00,263
only to find myself tied down
and imprisoned.

1091
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:02,974
Gosh. It's so stifling.

1092
01:00:06,311 --> 01:00:07,896
<i>May I have your attention please?</i>

1093
01:00:07,979 --> 01:00:09,731
<i>We have a medical emergency on board.</i>

1094
01:00:09,815 --> 01:00:12,025
<i>Any medical professionals,</i>
<i>please see a flight attendant.</i>

1095
01:00:12,109 --> 01:00:13,443
<i>Thank you.</i>

1096
01:00:15,237 --> 01:00:16,530
Any doctors or nurses?

1097
01:00:16,613 --> 01:00:18,240
Is anyone a doctor or a nurse?

1098
01:00:18,323 --> 01:00:19,366
Any doctors or nurses?

1099
01:00:19,449 --> 01:00:21,034
Is anyone a doctor or a nurse?

1100
01:00:22,244 --> 01:00:24,162
Is anyone a doctor or a nurse?

1101
01:00:27,958 --> 01:00:28,875
A doctor?

1102
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:30,877
We really appreciate you stepping up.

1103
01:00:32,671 --> 01:00:35,590
We were so worried.
Thank goodness we had a doctor on board.

1104
01:00:35,674 --> 01:00:37,300
You say a life is in grave danger.

1105
01:00:37,384 --> 01:00:40,590
It is man's duty to preserve
even the life of his enemy.

1106
01:00:40,679 --> 01:00:41,680
Eastern medicine?

1107
01:00:41,763 --> 01:00:44,099
I am known for my healing hands.

1108
01:00:44,182 --> 01:00:45,725
<i>Even during my palace maid days,</i>

1109
01:00:45,809 --> 01:00:48,770
<i>palace nurses lined up for me to prick</i>
<i>their fingers to relieve indigestion.</i>

1110
01:00:48,854 --> 01:00:50,355
One, two, three, four.

1111
01:00:50,438 --> 01:00:51,565
- Right here.
- Five, six.

1112
01:00:51,648 --> 01:00:53,692
- The doctor is here.
- Seven, eight. Three, two, three.

1113
01:00:53,775 --> 01:00:54,860
Six, seven, eight.

1114
01:00:54,943 --> 01:00:55,819
Cha Se-gye?

1115
01:00:57,529 --> 01:00:58,780
Hey, Cha Se-gye!

1116
01:00:58,864 --> 01:01:00,282
Why are you sprawled out like this?

1117
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:02,159
Do you know him? Thank goodness.

1118
01:01:02,868 --> 01:01:04,578
Pricking his finger will not be enough.

1119
01:01:05,579 --> 01:01:06,872
Cha Se-gye, breathe. Come on.

1120
01:01:06,955 --> 01:01:07,998
Cha Se-gye!

1121
01:01:08,081 --> 01:01:09,875
What are you doing? Please start CPR!

1122
01:01:09,958 --> 01:01:11,001
What? "Sipper"?

1123
01:01:11,084 --> 01:01:12,169
Hold on.

1124
01:01:12,252 --> 01:01:14,004
Oh no…

1125
01:01:14,087 --> 01:01:16,089
Come on, Cha Se-gye!

1126
01:01:16,173 --> 01:01:17,424
Breathe, come on!

1127
01:01:17,507 --> 01:01:18,800
Cha Se-gye!

1128
01:01:22,804 --> 01:01:25,182
<i>Passengers, the aircraft</i>
<i>is experiencing turbulence…</i>

1129
01:01:25,265 --> 01:01:26,766
What are you doing? Hurry!

1130
01:01:26,850 --> 01:01:28,935
<i>Please fasten your seatbelts.</i>

1131
01:01:30,020 --> 01:01:31,688
<i>Ladies and gentlemen…</i>

1132
01:01:34,065 --> 01:01:35,734
What the…

1133
01:01:35,817 --> 01:01:37,444
What are you doing right now?

1134
01:01:38,069 --> 01:01:39,154
Cha Se-gye!

1135
01:01:39,237 --> 01:01:41,531
Cha Se-gye, wake up!

1136
01:01:41,615 --> 01:01:43,116
Wake up!

1137
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:44,743
Cha Se-gye!

1138
01:01:45,952 --> 01:01:47,871
Come on, Cha Se-gye!

1139
01:01:57,339 --> 01:01:58,673
Cha Se-gye.

1140
01:01:58,757 --> 01:02:00,884
Are you finally coming to your senses?

1141
01:02:02,052 --> 01:02:05,889
Goodness, I really thought you were
about to cross into the afterlife.

1142
01:02:08,183 --> 01:02:09,476
You…

1143
01:02:11,061 --> 01:02:13,188
- Poison…
- What poison?

1144
01:02:13,897 --> 01:02:15,440
Tonic? Toxin?

1145
01:02:15,523 --> 01:02:17,609
I cannot hear you. Speak up!

1146
01:02:18,235 --> 01:02:19,444
Rat poison.

1147
01:02:19,527 --> 01:02:20,779
Rat poison?

1148
01:02:27,035 --> 01:02:28,954
You're toxic, like poison.

1149
01:02:34,459 --> 01:02:36,670
Cha Se-gye!

1150
01:02:37,295 --> 01:02:38,421
Have you gone mad?

1151
01:02:38,505 --> 01:02:39,589
Cha Se-gye!

1152
01:02:39,673 --> 01:02:42,884
Open your eyes! Cha Se-gye!

1153
01:02:43,593 --> 01:02:45,553
Cha Se-gye!

1154
01:02:45,637 --> 01:02:46,554
Where's the AED?

1155
01:02:47,180 --> 01:02:48,348
I have it.

1156
01:02:48,848 --> 01:02:51,977
No! Don't die, Cha Se-gye!

1157
01:02:52,060 --> 01:02:53,895
Cha Se-gye!

1158
01:03:00,568 --> 01:03:02,362
Cha Se-gye!

1159
01:03:02,445 --> 01:03:03,405
You cannot die!

1160
01:03:03,488 --> 01:03:06,116
Cha Se-gye, do not leave me!

1161
01:03:06,199 --> 01:03:08,576
No, please do not die!

1162
01:03:08,660 --> 01:03:10,870
- Everyone, step back.
- No, do not die!

1163
01:03:10,954 --> 01:03:13,290
- Cha Se-gye, no!
- One, two, three!

1164
01:03:13,373 --> 01:03:14,708
No--

1165
01:03:27,971 --> 01:03:28,847
Oh no…

1166
01:03:29,764 --> 01:03:31,016
<i>My welfare is my first priority.</i>

1167
01:03:31,099 --> 01:03:32,976
<i>And my second.</i>

1168
01:03:33,059 --> 01:03:36,146
<i>In this life, I will be sure</i>
<i>to guard my heart</i>

1169
01:03:36,229 --> 01:03:37,731
<i>and live out my days to the fullest.</i>

1170
01:03:58,752 --> 01:04:02,297
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1171
01:04:04,341 --> 01:04:05,550
Here.

1172
01:04:22,859 --> 01:04:24,903
Become my brother's lover.

1173
01:04:41,044 --> 01:04:43,546
You must have cherished this dog greatly.

1174
01:04:43,630 --> 01:04:45,715
I am sure it is grateful.

1175
01:04:47,967 --> 01:04:49,260
Thanks to you,

1176
01:04:49,344 --> 01:04:52,138
its life here was a little less lonely.

1177
01:04:59,938 --> 01:05:01,314
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

1178
01:05:03,358 --> 01:05:04,901
This flower suits you.

1179
01:05:04,984 --> 01:05:07,821
It stands out, so it is perfect for you.

1180
01:05:14,911 --> 01:05:17,038
Do not be too heartbroken.

1181
01:05:17,622 --> 01:05:22,168
Why not seek out a true companion
instead of a dog that cannot speak?

1182
01:05:22,252 --> 01:05:23,461
Shall I be

1183
01:05:23,545 --> 01:05:24,921
that companion for you?

1184
01:06:16,806 --> 01:06:19,559
<i>Have I finally crossed over</i>
<i>to the afterlife?</i>

1185
01:06:19,642 --> 01:06:22,061
Could this be paradise?

1186
01:06:22,145 --> 01:06:25,607
<i>If I am doing this, I might as well</i>
<i>go all out and show it all off.</i>

1187
01:06:25,690 --> 01:06:28,109
<i>Change her outfit. Next. Swap.</i>

1188
01:06:28,193 --> 01:06:29,611
Are your eyes possessed or something?

1189
01:06:29,694 --> 01:06:31,779
She's the only thing I can see right now!

1190
01:06:32,614 --> 01:06:34,616
<i>Why are you nitpicking</i>
<i>every little thing today?</i>

1191
01:06:34,699 --> 01:06:37,619
<i>Just because I rejected your affections,</i>
<i>you hound me all damn day?</i>

1192
01:06:37,702 --> 01:06:39,537
<i>I am truly glad to be alive.</i>

1193
01:06:39,621 --> 01:06:40,788
Drink up!

1194
01:06:40,872 --> 01:06:43,333
It seems the time has come.
Take care of her quietly.

1195
01:06:43,416 --> 01:06:45,168
<i>Is Seo-ri still not answering?</i>

1196
01:06:45,752 --> 01:06:47,587
You saw her? Where?

1197
01:06:47,670 --> 01:06:49,547
Where is she right now?

1198
01:06:52,926 --> 01:06:54,928
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim
